Topshop tycoon Sir Philip Green has put struggling high street store BHS up for sale after a sales dip and pre-tax loss of £69.9million.

The billionaire businessman's decision to put the retail chain, with more than 185 stores, up for auction, signals the break-up of one of Britain's best-known high street empires.

It comes after the 62-year-old received several serious approaches in the past few months, senior city sources told the Sunday Times.

