Despite a near 1 per cent rise in sales to £2.7billion Bhs slid further into the red. The group also did not pay out a dividend for the ninth year in a row.

Sir Philip has rejected previous offers for BHS on price grounds. But, for the first time he is understood to have received a handful of bids that match his expectations.

The chain has attracted interest from rivals such as Primark, and late in 2013 it was briefly targeted by the South African billionaire Christo Wiese.

American hedge fund Apollo and the turnaround firm Hilco, which took over HMV, are also believed to have looked at it. 

BHS has 150 stores with permission to sell food and one approach is believed to have come from a grocery retailer.

